reviews.text: Worplesdon is located near the town of Mayford and is served by Southwest Trains only. Worplesdon is a lovely station located in the town with the same name. The station is awesome but it has its issues, the station is falling apart and not a lot of trains stop here, but the station has has its bright sides, the station is at least clean and signs are legible, the area is also quiet and peaceful.
An attractive traditional railway station on the scenic Pompy Line. Steam trains pass through regularly!

Whilst the station was kept in a good condition, there were quite a few issues. Disabled access to this station is a joke. You cannot access the ticket office (when it's open, of course) and thus, enter the station without going up a few steps. Platform 2 towards Guildford requires taking a footbridge. There's a toilet in the building, albeit, not wheelchair accessible. 

Seating is minimal, with only a single shelter and seating. A few good things is at least the staff here were very nice and that the platforms are long enough for the typical 12 car services here.
Basic but lovely station BUT tickets cost an arm and a leg
